activities.instructions: Stand with one dumbbell in each hand so that they are touching your sides. While keeping your arms almost straight, raise the dumbbells up to the sides until they are just below shoulder level.
activities.name: Dumbbell Side Raise

activities.instructions: While seated, position the dumbbells at shoulder level with your palms facing in. As you press the dumbbells up, rotate your arms so that your palms are facing outwards at the end of the movement.
activities.name: Arnold Dumbbell Press (Seated)

activities.instructions: Sit on a bench and grab a dumbbell. Pull it out to your side until your arm is at shoulder level, and then lower it back down.
activities.name: Dumbbell Side Raise (Seated)

activities.instructions: Sit on a bench with the barbell resting on your upper chest. Keep your abs flexed and back straight as you press the weight straight up above your head, and then lower it back down.
activities.name: Barbell Shoulder Press (Seated)

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab an Ez-Bar at the inner handles so that your palms are facing slightly inwards. Lift the barbell all the way up to your chin and then lower it back down.
activities.name: Upright EZ-Bar Row

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a dumbbell in each hand. While keeping your arms straight, lift the dumbbells forward until they're at shoulder level, then lower them back down.
activities.name: Dumbbell Front Raise

activities.instructions: Bend over and grab opposite cable handle in each hand. Begin to pull them to your sides in line with your shoulders until your arms are at shoulder level.
activities.name: Cable Rear Delt Fly

activities.instructions: Stand up in a cable machine with a rope attached to the handle. The handle should be at shoulder height. Grab it with both hands to that your palms are facing inwards against each other. Tuck your elbows in at your sides and push the rope down towards your thighs, then lower it back up.
activities.name: Cable Pushdown (with Rope Handle)

activities.instructions: Lie down flat on a bench. Grab a barbell at a shoulder wide grip. Position yourself under the barbell so that it is above your chest. Bend your elbows but keep them stationary and lower the barbell down behind your head until your triceps are fully stretched. Then push it back up so that it ends up above your chest.
activities.name: Lying Barbell Skull Crusher

activities.instructions: Stand in a cable machine with a bar attached to the handle. The handle should be at shoulder height. Grab it with overhand grip so that your palms are facing downwards towards the floor. Tuck your elbows in at your sides and push the bar down towards your thighs, then lower it back up.
activities.name: Cable Pushdown (with Bar Handle)

activities.instructions: Form a diamond on the floor in front of you with your hands, do this by bringing your hands together so that the tops of your index fingers meet and edges of thumbs also meet. Then lower yourself down as you would in a regular pushup and then push yourself back up.
activities.name: Diamond Pushup

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a barbell at a little wider than shoulder width grip. Shrug the weight up and then lower it back down so that your arms are fully stretched. Try not to bend your arms as you do the movement.
activities.name: Barbell Shrug

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a dumbbell in each hand. Shrug them up to your sides and then lower them back down until your arms are fully stretched. Try not to bend your arms as you do the movement.
activities.name: Dumbbell Shrug

activities.instructions: Grab a barbell at a little wider than a shoulder width grip behind you. Simply shrug the barbell up and then lower it back down until your arms are fully stretched. Try not to bend your arms as you do the movement.
activities.name: Barbell Shrug (Behind the Back)

activities.instructions: Sit down in a pulldown machine with the paddings adjusted so that they comfortably hold your legs down when you're holding the bar. Grab the wide pulldown bar with your palms facing forward at a little more than shoulder width apart. Slightly lean back so that you arch your lower back and puff your chest up, then pull the bar down by drawing your shoulders and upper arms down and back. Once the bar touches your chest, slowly begin to raise the bar back to the starting position, allowing your lat muscles to stretch out more the further up you go.
activities.name: Wide-Grip Machine Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Sit in a pulldown machine but rather than pulling towards your upper chest, pull the bar towards your neck. Stopping just before it touches it.
activities.name: Machine Lat Pulldown (Behind the Neck)

activities.instructions: Stand in a pulldown machine and grab the bar at a shoulder wide width. Begin pushing downwards with your arms straight throughout the movement, stop when you're about to reach your thighs.
activities.name: Straight-Arm Machine Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Grab a dumbbell in each hand and bend over with a straight back. Pull the dumbbells towards your shoulders and lower them back down.
activities.name: Dumbbell Rear Delt Row

performanceTarget.note: Chest supported on incline, hammer into underhand grip, 4:0:1:0

activities.instructions: Place a dumbbell on the floor and position yourself over a bench with one knee on the bench and the other one on the floor. Bend over forward with a straight back, flex your abs and grab the dumbbell. Begin pulling it to your side towards your abs. Then lower it back down.
activities.name: Single-Arm Dumbbell Row on Bench

activities.instructions: Sit down on a bench in front of a cable machine. Pull the handle towards your lower belly while keeping your back straight. Then slowly let the handle back and let your arms stretch out fully.
activities.name: Cable Row

activities.instructions: Stand up in the machine with the pads on your shoulders, unrack the weight and lower it all the way down so that you feel a good stretch in your calves. Push it all the way up and then lower it back down slowly, pausing at the bottom for a second or two to avoid pushing with your achilles heel.
activities.name: Machine Calf Raise

activities.instructions: Stand up in the machine with the pads on your shoulders, unrack the weight and lower it all the way down so that you feel a good stretch in your calves. Push it all the way up and then lower it back down slowly, pausing at the bottom for a second or two to avoid pushing with your achilles heel.
activities.name: Machine Calf Raise

activities.instructions: Put the barbell on your upper back and squat down until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Barbell Squat

activities.instructions: Adjust the machine so that you're sitting comfortably and the seat ends just before your knee. Fully extend your legs while keeping the rest of your body stationary, then lower them back down to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Leg Extension

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine and put your feet up against the plate as if you were doing a Squat. Unrack the weight and lower it down until your knee is at a 90 degree angle, then push it back up. Stop just before your legs are fully straight to relieve your knees from extra stress.
activities.name: Machine Leg Press

activities.instructions: The technique is identical to a regular Squat, but with extra stability from the machine. Stand in the machine with the shoulder pads on your shoulders, unrack the weight and sit down until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then stand back up.
activities.name: Machine Hack Squat

activities.instructions: Sit in the machine and adjust it so that you feel a minor stretch as you put your legs into the starting position. Push your legs together and then slowly let them back out again until you return to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Thigh Adduction (In)

activities.instructions: Sit comfortably in the machine and begin the movement by pushing your legs out to your sides as far as you can. Then return them to the starting position. All of this while keeping your upper body stationary.
activities.name: Machine Thigh Abduction (Out)

activities.instructions: Stand in a pulldown machine and grab the bar at a shoulder wide width. Begin pushing downwards with your arms straight throughout the movement, stop when you're about to reach your thighs.
activities.name: Straight-Arm Machine Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Sit down on a bench in front of a cable machine. Pull the handle towards your lower belly while keeping your back straight. Then slowly let the handle back and let your arms stretch out fully.
activities.name: Cable Row

activities.instructions: Grab a barbell with a little wider than a shoulder width grip. While keeping your back straight and abs flexed, bend over until your back is at a 45 degree angle towards the floor. Pull the barbell towards your abs and stop when they touch, then let the barbell back down so you end up with your arms fully stretched out.
activities.name: Bent-Over Barbell Row

activities.instructions: Adjust the machine so that your legs fit comfortably under the rack. Grab the bar and sit down with your legs under the rack. With a slight arch in your lower back begin pulling down towards your upper chest. After touching your chest with the bar, slowly return it until your arms and lats are fully stretched.
activities.name: Machine Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Put a pair of dumbbells on the floor in front of you on the floor. Position your feet at hip width apart, slightly bend your knees, bend over with a straight back, and grab both dumbbells with a neutral grip. Pull both dumbbells towards the side of your abs and then slowly let them back down until your arms are straight.
activities.name: Bent-Over Dumbbell Row

activities.instructions: Stand up in a smith machine with a plate or some elevated object on the floor in front of you. Stand on it with the front of your foot and push yourself up through your foot. Then lower yourself back down. Tip: Stop for 1 second at the bottom of the movement.
activities.name: Smith Machine Calf Raise

Push it all the way up and then lower it back down slowly, pausing at the bottom for a second or two to avoid pushing with your achilles heel.
activities.name: Machine Calf Raise

activities.instructions: Hang freely from a pull-up-bar and raise your legs straight forward as if you were doing a curl with your whole body.
activities.name: Hanging Leg Raise

activities.instructions: Stand on your knees in a cable machine with a cable attached to the handle. Grab the cable with both hands at the sides of your head. Pull the cable down as if you were doing an upside-down sit-up. Then let the cable back up. Keep hips stationary throughout the movement.
activities.name: Cable Crunch

activities.instructions: Sit and grab the barbell with an underhand grip. Rest your arms on your thighs and let it roll all the way out to your fingers. Then squeeze it with your fingers so that the barbell ends up in the middle of your palm again.
activities.name: Barbell Wrist Curl

activities.instructions: Sit and grab a dumbbell with an underhand grip. Rest your arm on your thigh and let the dumbbell roll all the way out to your fingers. Then squeeze it with your fingers so that the dumbbell ends up in the middle of your palm again.
activities.name: Dumbbell Wrist Curl

activities.instructions: Lie down on a regular bench with one dumbbell in each hand. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them out to your sides. You can imagine yourself hugging a giant tree on the way up, and then letting go as you lower them down. Go all the way down until your elbows are at the same level as your body. Tip: Squeeze your chest together at the top of the movement as if you were squeezing a football!

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a cable handle. Raise it to your side until your arm is at shoulder level.

activities.instructions: Sit on a bench with one dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level. Press the dumbbells up over your head and then lower them back down until they're at shoulder level again.
activities.name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press (Seated)

activities.instructions: Stand in a cable machine and grab the handle near one of your sides at a time. Pull it forward until it's at shoulder height and then lower it back down.
activities.name: Cable Front Raise

activities.instructions: Stand with one dumbbell in each hand so that they are touching your sides. While keeping your arms almost straight, raise the dumbbells up to the sides until they are just below shoulder level.
activities.name: Dumbbell Side Raise

activities.instructions: Sit comfortably in the machine with your upper arms resting against the padding. Grab onto the handles and curl the weight all the way up, and then lower it back down slowly until your arms are fully stretched.

Pause for a second or two in the bottom of the movement so that the weight doesn't get pushed up with the help of your achilles heel.

activities.instructions: Lay down flat on the floor with your legs bent. Thrust your hips towards the ceiling as far as you can and keep it in the top position for a second or two. Then release it back down to the floor again. You've just completed a repetition.

activities.instructions: Stand in a cable machine with a bar attached to the handle. The handle should be at shoulder height. Jump up into the starting position where your arms are straight, and lower yourself back down to the point where your elbows point towards the ceiling. If you feel shoulder or elbow discomfort it is recommended to stop when your arms are at a 90 degree angle. Push yourself back up until your arms are straight. Keep elbows tucked in as much as you can throughout the movement to target the triceps.

activities.instructions: Stand up with one dumbbell in each hand and get them to their starting positions right above your head by swinging them up. Your arms should be straight and pointing up. Slowly begin to lower them straight back with your elbows stationary throughout the movement. Lower them until they're at shoulder height. Then press them back up.
activities.name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension

activities.instructions: Kneel down on the floor in a cable machine and have the handle at shoulder height. Grab it with both hands so that your palms are facing inwards and tuck your elbows in at your sides. Push it down towards your thighs and then slowly let it back up.

Keep the elbow stationary while you slowly lower the dumbbell back until it reaches shoulder height. Then push it back up. Switch hand after you've finished your repetitions.
activities.name: Single-Arm Dumbbell Triceps Extension

activities.instructions: Adjust the machine so that your legs fit comfortably under the rack. Grab the bar and sit down with your legs under the rack. With a slight arch in your lower back begin pulling down towards your upper chest. After touching your chest with the bar, slowly return it until your arms and lats are fully stretched.
activities.name: Machine Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Place a dumbbell on the floor and position yourself over a bench with one knee on the bench and the other one on the floor. Bend over forward with a straight back, flex your abs and grab the dumbbell. Begin pulling it to your side towards your abs. Then lower it back down.
activities.name: Single-Arm Dumbbell Row on Bench

activities.instructions: Stand in a pulldown machine and grab the bar at a shoulder wide width. Begin pushing downwards with your arms straight throughout the movement, stop when you're about to reach your thighs.
activities.name: Straight-Arm Machine Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Grab a barbell with a little wider than a shoulder width grip. While keeping your back straight and abs flexed, bend over until your back is at a 45 degree angle towards the floor. Pull the barbell towards your abs and stop when they touch, then let the barbell back down so you end up with your arms fully stretched out.
activities.name: Bent-Over Barbell Row

activities.instructions: Sit down in a pulldown machine with the paddings adjusted so that they comfortably hold your legs down when you're holding the bar. Grab the wide pulldown bar with your palms facing forward at a little more than shoulder width apart. Slightly lean back so that you arch your lower back and puff your chest up, then pull the bar down by drawing your shoulders and upper arms down and back. Once the bar touches your chest, slowly begin to raise the bar back to the starting position, allowing your lat muscles to stretch out more the further up you go.
activities.name: Wide-Grip Machine Lat Pulldown

performanceTarget.note: 4Reps wide grip, 6reps wide grip behind neck, 8 reps underhand close grip, drop sets

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a barbell at a little wider than shoulder width grip. Shrug the weight up and then lower it back down so that your arms are fully stretched. Try not to bend your arms as you do the movement.
activities.name: Barbell Shrug

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a dumbbell in each hand. Shrug them up to your sides and then lower them back down until your arms are fully stretched. Try not to bend your arms as you do the movement.
activities.name: Dumbbell Shrug

activities.instructions: Lie down on the machine with the pads just below your calves and grab onto the handles at your sides. While keeping your upper legs static, curl the weight up as far as you can and keep your upper body stationary. Then lower the weight back down until your legs are fully stretched.
activities.name: Machine Lying Leg Curl

activities.instructions: Stand up in a shoulder wide stance and grab the barbell at a shoulder wide grip. Bend over forward and lower the barbell all the way down as far as you can or until your back is parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Stiff-Leg Deadlift (Wide Stance)

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine and grab the handles at your sides. Place the padding just below your calves so that your legs are fully extended for the starting position. Curl them down until you have a 90 degree angle at your knee and then return back to the fully extended position.
activities.name: Machine Leg Curl

activities.instructions: Put the barbell on your upper back and squat down until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Barbell Squat

activities.instructions: Place a flat bench behind you and grab a pair of dumbbells. Extend one leg back at a time and place the top of the foot on bench. Squat down until your rear knee almost touches the floor, return to starting position. Keep your torso upright throughout the movement and swap to opposite leg after you're done with your repetitions.
activities.name: Bulgarian Split Squat

activities.instructions: Lay down flat on the floor with your legs bent. Thrust your hips towards the ceiling as far as you can and keep it in the top position for a second or two. Then release it back down to the floor again. You've just completed a repetition.
activities.name: Bodyweight Bridge

activities.instructions: Sit comfortably in the machine and begin the movement by pushing your legs out to your sides as far as you can. Then return them to the starting position. All of this while keeping your upper body stationary.
activities.name: Machine Thigh Abduction (Out)

activities.instructions: Stand in a smith machine and position yourself so that the barbell is resting on your upper back. Squat down until your legs are parallel to the floor and then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Smith Machine Squat

activities.instructions: Sit on a bench and grab a dumbbell. Pull it out to your side until your arm is at shoulder level, and then lower it back down.
activities.name: Dumbbell Side Raise (Seated)

activities.instructions: Stand with one dumbbell in each hand so that they are touching your sides. While keeping your arms almost straight, raise one dumbbell at a time to your side until it's just below shoulder level. Alternate arms between repetitions.
activities.name: Alternating Dumbbell Side Raise

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a dumbbell in each hand. While keeping your arms straight, lift the dumbbells forward until they're at shoulder level, then lower them back down.
activities.name: Dumbbell Front Raise

activities.instructions: Stand up with a barbell resting on your upper chest. Keep your abs flexed and back straight as you press the weight straight up above your head, and then lower it back down.
activities.name: Barbell Shoulder Press

activities.instructions: Bend over and grab opposite cable handle in each hand. Begin to pull them to your sides in line with your shoulders until your arms are at shoulder level.
activities.name: Cable Rear Delt Fly

performanceTarget.note: Bent over rear delt dumbbell fly, drop

activities.instructions: Sit comfortably in the machine with your upper arms resting against the padding. Grab onto the handles and curl the weight all the way up, and then lower it back down slowly until your arms are fully stretched.
activities.name: Machine Preacher Curl

activities.instructions: Grab a barbell with a reverse grip at shoulder width so that your palms are facing inwards against you. Let the barbell rest against your thighs at the bottom of the movement, then curl the weight up until it's at shoulder level. Lower it back down.
activities.name: Reverse Barbell Curl

activities.instructions: Stand up with one dumbbell in each hand. Keep your elbows tucked in at your sides as you curl the dumbbells up until they're at shoulder level. Then lower them back down to the sides of your thighs.
activities.name: Dumbbell Curl

activities.instructions: Stand up with one dumbbell in each hand. Grab them as if you were grabbing two bottles so that your palms are facing inwards. Keep your palms facing inwards and alternate between the dumbbells as you curl one at a time all the way up, then lower it back down.
activities.name: Alternating Dumbbell Hammer Curl

activities.instructions: Sit on a bench with one dumbbell on the floor in between your legs. Grab it with one arm at a time and curl it up while supporting your elbow with your inner thigh.
activities.name: Dumbbell Concentration Curl

activities.instructions: Sit down with the pads on your upper thighs and unrack the weight. Lower it all the way down so that you feel a full stretch of your calves, then push it all the way up and return back down. Pause for a second or two in the bottom of the movement so that the weight doesn't get pushed up with the help of your achilles heel.
activities.name: Machine Calf Raise (Seated)

activities.instructions: Stand up in a smith machine with a plate or some elevated object on the floor in front of you. Stand on it with the front of your foot and push yourself up through your foot. Then lower yourself back down. Tip: Stop for 1 second at the bottom of the movement.
activities.name: Smith Machine Calf Raise

activities.instructions: Lie down flat on the floor with a weight plate or dumbbell behind your head. Hold onto it while keeping it behind your neck above the floor and lift your upper body towards the ceiling.
activities.name: Weighted Crunch

activities.instructions: Grab onto the handles and keep your elbows tucked in at your sides. Begin the movement by pulling downwards with your abs, slightly rounding your lower back in the movement.

Machines can differ from each other but in general you should adjust the seat so that you're seated with your back against the padding and have the handles just below shoulder height. 

Grab onto them and push them in towards each other as if you were hugging someone in front of you. Pause when the handles reach each other and then slowly return them back to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Fly

activities.instructions: Lie down on a regular bench with one dumbbell in each hand. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them out to your sides. You can imagine yourself hugging a giant tree on the way up, and then letting go as you lower them down. Go all the way down until your elbows are at the same level as your body. Tip: Squeeze your chest together at the top of the movement as if you were squeezing a football!

activities.name: Machine Bench Press

activities.name: Cable Pushdown (with Rope Handle)

activities.instructions: Sit on a bench with a barbell positioned above your head. Keep arms straight at the start of the movement and begin by bending your arms at the elbow. Lower the weight down until it reaches your neck, then push it back up.
activities.name: Barbell Triceps Extension (Seated)

activities.instructions: Stand in a cable machine with a bar attached to the handle. The handle should be at shoulder height. activities.instructions: Lie down flat on a bench. Grab a barbell at a shoulder wide grip. Position yourself under the barbell so that it is above your chest. Bend your elbows but keep them stationary and lower the barbell down behind your head until your triceps are fully stretched. Then push it back up so that it ends up above your chest.
activities.name: Lying Barbell Skull Crusher

activities.instructions: Kneel down on a bench with one leg and keep the other one on the floor. Grab a dumbbell with one arm at a time and tuck your elbow in at your side. Then "kick" it back by lifting it up behind you. Finish the movement by lowering the weight back down. Tip: Bend slightly forward so that your upper arm is a little angled upwards.
activities.name: Dumbbell Kickback

activities.instructions: Sit in the machine and adjust the pad so that you can reach the handles while your chest is pressed up against it. Grab the handles and begin pulling back. Try to keep your elbows as close to your sides as possible and imagine that you're pulling with your elbows, not your arms. Once you've reached as far back as you can go, slowly begin to let the handles back until your arms are fully stretched. Repeat.

activities.name: Straight-Arm Machine Lat Pulldown

Position your feet at hip width apart, slightly bend your knees, bend over with a straight back, and grab both dumbbells with a neutral grip. Pull both dumbbells towards the side of your abs and then slowly let them back down until your arms are straight.
activities.name: Bent-Over Dumbbell Row

activities.instructions: Adjust a pulldown machine and replace the bar with a V-Bar. Grab onto it and pull down towards your upper chest and then slowly let it back up until your arms are fully stretched.

activities.instructions: Sit down on a bench in front of a cable machine. Pull the handle towards your lower belly while keeping your back straight. Then slowly let the handle back and let your arms stretch out fully.

activities.name: Cable Pushdown (Kneeling)

activities.instructions: Lay down flat on the floor with your legs bent. Thrust your hips towards the ceiling as far as you can and keep it in the top position for a second or two. Then release it back down to the floor again. You've just completed a repetition.
activities.name: Bodyweight Bridge

activities.instructions: Place a flat bench behind you and grab a pair of dumbbells. Extend one leg back at a time and place the top of the foot on bench. Squat down until your rear knee almost touches the floor, return to starting position. Keep your torso upright throughout the movement and swap to opposite leg after you're done with your repetitions.
activities.name: Bulgarian Split Squat

activities.instructions: Put the barbell on your upper back and squat down until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Barbell Squat

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine and grab the handles at your sides. Place the padding just below your calves so that your legs are fully extended for the starting position. Curl them down until you have a 90 degree angle at your knee and then return back to the fully extended position.
activities.name: Machine Leg Curl

activities.instructions: Lie down on the machine with the pads just below your calves and grab onto the handles at your sides. While keeping your upper legs static, curl the weight up as far as you can and keep your upper body stationary. Then lower the weight back down until your legs are fully stretched.
activities.name: Machine Lying Leg Curl

performanceTarget.note: reverse decline bench dumbbell leg curl 1212

activities.instructions: Stand up in a shoulder wide stance and grab the barbell at a shoulder wide grip. Bend over forward and lower the barbell all the way down as far as you can or until your back is parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Stiff-Leg Deadlift (Wide Stance)

activities.instructions:
Machines can differ from each other but in general you should adjust the seat so that you're seated with your back against the padding and have the handles just below shoulder height. 

Grab onto them and push them in towards each other as if you were hugging someone in front of you. Pause when the handles reach each other and then slowly return them back to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Fly

activities.instructions: Lie down on an inclined bench with one dumbbell in each hand with a hammer grip, i.e., your palms should be facing inwards towards each other. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them all the way down towards your upper chest. Then push them back up. Tip: Kick the dumbbells up to starting position with the help of your thighs.
activities.name: Incline Dumbbell Bench Press (with Hammer Grip)

activities.instructions: Lie down flat on the floor with one dumbbell at each of your sides. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then lower them down towards your chest, then push them back up. Hint: If you're using heavy dumbbells you can kick them up using your thighs.
activities.name: Dumbbell Floor Press

activities.instructions: Lie down on a declined bench with one dumbbell in each hand resting at your lower chest. Begin the movement by pushing them up to the starting position with your arms straight. Then begin to lower them out to your sides until your elbows are at the same level as your body, then push them back together. Tip: Squeeze your chest together at the top of the movement as if you were squeezing a football!
activities.name: Decline Dumbbell Fly

activities.instructions: Lie flat on a bench and hold onto it at the sides near your head. Lift your lower body straight up in the air so that the only part touching the bench is your upper back and head, then lower it back down. Tip: Turn the movement around just before your legs touch the bench at the end of the movement.
activities.name: Dragon Fly

performanceTarget.note: Dumbbell fly press - pronate fly into reverse grip press 4010

activities.instructions: Lie down on a declined bench with one dumbbell in each hand. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them down towards your lower chest. Then push them back up. Tip: Kick the dumbbells up to starting position with the help of your thighs.
activities.name: Decline Dumbbell Bench Press

performanceTarget.note: Replace with Decline barbell dang it 1210

activities.instructions: Grab the ab roller and position yourself on the floor. Roll the ab roller away from you until your body is fully stretched out and then roll it back towards you so that you end up in the same position as you started in. Keep abs tight throughout the movement.
activities.name: Ab Roller

activities.instructions: Sit and grab the barbell with an underhand grip. Rest your arms on your thighs and let it roll all the way out to your fingers. Then squeeze it with your fingers so that the barbell ends up in the middle of your palm again.
activities.name: Barbell Wrist Curl

activities.instructions: Hang freely from a pull-up-bar and raise your legs straight forward as if you were doing a curl with your whole body.
activities.name: Hanging Leg Raise

activities.instructions: Sit and grab a dumbbell with an underhand grip. Rest your arm on your thigh and let the dumbbell roll all the way out to your fingers. Then squeeze it with your fingers so that the dumbbell ends up in the middle of your palm again.
activities.name: Dumbbell Wrist Curl

activities.instructions: Grab a barbell with a little wider than a shoulder width grip. While keeping your back straight and abs flexed, bend over until your back is at a 45 degree angle towards the floor. Pull the barbell towards your abs and stop when they touch, then let the barbell back down so you end up with your arms fully stretched out.
activities.name: Bent-Over Barbell Row

activities.instructions: Adjust a pulldown machine and replace the bar with a V-Bar. Grab onto it and pull down towards your upper chest and then slowly let it back up until your arms are fully stretched.
activities.name: Machine V-Bar Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Sit down in a pulldown machine with the paddings adjusted so that they comfortably hold your legs down when you're holding the bar. Grab the wide pulldown bar with your palms facing forward at a little more than shoulder width apart. Slightly lean back so that you arch your lower back and puff your chest up, then pull the bar down by drawing your shoulders and upper arms down and back. Once the bar touches your chest, slowly begin to raise the bar back to the starting position, allowing your lat muscles to stretch out more the further up you go.
activities.name: Wide-Grip Machine Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Grab a dumbbell in each hand and bend over with a straight back. Pull the dumbbells towards your shoulders and lower them back down.
activities.name: Dumbbell Rear Delt Row

activities.instructions: Sit down on a bench in front of a cable machine. Pull the handle towards your lower belly while keeping your back straight. Then slowly let the handle back and let your arms stretch out fully.
activities.name: Cable Row

performanceTarget.note: Seated underhand grip 1212 Superset with next

activities.instructions: Stand in a pulldown machine and grab the bar at a shoulder wide width. Begin pushing downwards with your arms straight throughout the movement, stop when you're about to reach your thighs.
activities.name: Straight-Arm Machine Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Hang freely from a pull-up-bar with a little wider than shoulder width grip. Your palms should be facing forward, away from you. Pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar. Then lower yourself back down until your arms are fully stretched. See Weighted Pull-Ups if you are using additional weights.
activities.name: Pullup

activities.instructions: Sit down with the pads on your upper thighs and unrack the weight. Lower it all the way down so that you feel a full stretch of your calves, then push it all the way up and return back down. Pause for a second or two in the bottom of the movement so that the weight doesn't get pushed up with the help of your achilles heel.
activities.name: Machine Calf Raise (Seated)

activities.instructions: Stand up in the machine with the pads on your shoulders, unrack the weight and lower it all the way down so that you feel a good stretch in your calves. Push it all the way up and then lower it back down slowly, pausing at the bottom for a second or two to avoid pushing with your achilles heel.
activities.name: Machine Calf Raise

activities.instructions: Adjust the machine so that you're sitting comfortably and the seat ends just before your knee. Fully extend your legs while keeping the rest of your body stationary, then lower them back down to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Leg Extension

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine and put your feet up against the plate as if you were doing a Squat. Unrack the weight and lower it down until your knee is at a 90 degree angle, then push it back up. Stop just before your legs are fully straight to relieve your knees from extra stress.
activities.name: Machine Leg Press

performanceTarget.note: Feet touching and low on platform 4010

activities.instructions: The technique is identical to a regular Squat, but with extra stability from the machine. Stand in the machine with the shoulder pads on your shoulders, unrack the weight and sit down until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then stand back up.
activities.name: Machine Hack Squat

activities.instructions: Grab a dumbbell and position it at the same height as your shoulders. Hold it with both hands and begin to squat down until your legs are parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Goblet Squat

activities.instructions: Adjust the machine so that you're sitting comfortably and the seat ends just before your knee. Fully extend you leg while keeping the rest of your body stationary, then lower it back down to the starting position. Alternate leg when you've finished the desired number of repetition.
activities.name: Machine Single-Leg Extension

activities.instructions: Sit comfortably in the machine and begin the movement by pushing your legs out to your sides as far as you can. Then return them to the starting position. All of this while keeping your upper body stationary.
activities.name: Machine Thigh Abduction (Out)

activities.instructions: Sit in the machine and adjust it so that you feel a minor stretch as you put your legs into the starting position. Push your legs together and then slowly let them back out again until you return to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Thigh Adduction (In)

activities.instructions: Sit on a bench and grab a cable handle. Pull it out to your side until your arm is at shoulder level, and then lower it back down.
activities.name: Cable Side Raise (Seated)

activities.instructions: While seated, position the dumbbells at shoulder level with your palms facing in. As you press the dumbbells up, rotate your arms so that your palms are facing outwards at the end of the movement.
activities.name: Arnold Dumbbell Press (Seated)

activities.instructions: Grab a dumbbell in each hand and keep them at your sides. Alternate between them as you lift them forward until they're at shoulder height and then lower them back down.
activities.name: Alternating Dumbbell Front Raise

activities.instructions: Stand in a cable machine with the handle at shoulder level. Pull it towards your shoulders and let it back.
activities.name: Cable Rear Delt Row

performanceTarget.note: 1212 side lateral machine rear delt fly

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a barbell at a little wider than shoulder width grip. Shrug the weight up and then lower it back down so that your arms are fully stretched. Try not to bend your arms as you do the movement.
activities.name: Barbell Shrug

performanceTarget.note: snatch grip 1212, super set with weighted wrestling bridge

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a dumbbell in each hand. Shrug them up to your sides and then lower them back down until your arms are fully stretched. Try not to bend your arms as you do the movement.
activities.name: Dumbbell Shrug

performanceTarget.note: 4012 superset with weighted front neck raise

activities.instructions: Stand up with one dumbbell in each hand. Keep your elbows tucked in at your sides and alternate between the dumbbells as you curl one at a time up. As you lower it down prepare to curl the other one up.
activities.name: Alternating Dumbbell Curl

activities.instructions: Stand up in a cable machine with a rope attached to the handle. The handle should be at shoulder height. Grab it with both hands to that your palms are facing inwards against each other. Tuck your elbows in at your sides and push the rope down towards your thighs, then lower it back up.
activities.name: Cable Pushdown (with Rope Handle)

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a barbell at a little wider than a shoulder width grip. Keep your elbows tucked in at your sides as you curl the barbell all the way up until it reaches shoulder level. Then lower it back down to your thighs.
activities.name: Wide-Grip Barbell Curl

activities.instructions: Stand in a cable machine with a bar attached to the handle. The handle should be at shoulder height. Grab it with overhand grip so that your palms are facing downwards towards the floor. Tuck your elbows in at your sides and push the bar down towards your thighs, then lower it back up.
activities.name: Cable Pushdown (with Bar Handle)

activities.instructions: Stand up in a cable machine and replace the handle with a rope. Grab the rope as if you were grabbing a bottle and curl it up. Then lower it back down.
activities.name: Cable Hammer Curl

activities.instructions: Stand up with one dumbbell in each hand and get them to their starting positions right above your head by swinging them up. Your arms should be straight and pointing up. Slowly begin to lower them straight back with your elbows stationary throughout the movement. Lower them until they're at shoulder height. Then press them back up.
activities.name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension

activities.instructions: Stand up right next to a cable machine with a bar attached to it. Grab it and keep your elbows tucked in to your sides, then simply curl the weight up to shoulder level. Lower it back down slowly until your arms are fully extended.
activities.name: Cable Curl

performanceTarget.note: Double arm overhead cable curl 1212 Super Set

activities.instructions: Kneel down on the floor in a cable machine and have the handle at shoulder height. Grab it with both hands so that your palms are facing inwards and tuck your elbows in at your sides. Push it down towards your thighs and then slowly let it back up.
activities.name: Cable Pushdown (Kneeling)

activities.instructions: Stand up with one dumbbell in each hand. Grab them as if you were grabbing two bottles so that your palms are facing inwards. Keep your palms facing inwards and curl the dumbbells all the way up, then lower them back down.
activities.name: Dumbbell Hammer Curl

Squat down until your rear knee almost touches the floor, return to starting position. activities.name: Bulgarian Split Squat

activities.name: Bodyweight Bridge

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine and put your feet up against the plate as if you were doing a Squat. Unrack the weight and lower it down until your knee is at a 90 degree angle, then push it back up. Stop just before your legs are fully straight to relieve your knees from extra stress.
activities.name: Machine Leg Press

activities.instructions: Stand in a smith machine and position yourself so that the barbell is resting on your upper back. Squat down until your legs are parallel to the floor and then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Smith Machine Squat

activities.instructions: Lie down on the machine with the pads just below your calves and grab onto the handles at your sides. While keeping your upper legs static, curl the weight up as far as you can and keep your upper body stationary. Then lower the weight back down until your legs are fully stretched.
activities.name: Machine Lying Leg Curl

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine and grab the handles at your sides. Place the padding just below your calves so that your legs are fully extended for the starting position. Curl them down until you have a 90 degree angle at your knee and then return back to the fully extended position.
activities.name: Machine Leg Curl

activities.instructions: Stand up in a shoulder wide stance and grab the barbell at a shoulder wide grip. Bend over forward and lower the barbell all the way down as far as you can or until your back is parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Stiff-Leg Deadlift (Wide Stance)

activities.instructions: Place yourself under the barbell so that it is resting on your upper back. Keep everything stationary and begin to bend over, keeping your abs flexed. Stop when your torso is parallel to the floor and return to upright position.
activities.name: Good Mornings

activities.instructions: Lie down on a declined bench with one dumbbell in each hand resting at your lower chest. Begin the movement by pushing them up to the starting position with your arms straight. Then begin to lower them out to your sides until your elbows are at the same level as your body, then push them back together. Tip: Squeeze your chest together at the top of the movement as if you were squeezing a football!
activities.name: Decline Dumbbell Fly

activities.instructions: Lie down on an inclined bench with one dumbbell in each hand. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them down towards your upper chest. Then push them back up. Tip: Kick the dumbbells up to starting position with the help of your thighs.
activities.name: Incline Dumbbell Bench Press

activities.instructions: Lie down on an inclined bench under a barbell. Preferably in a rack for your own safety. Then un-rack the barbell and begin to lower it towards your upper chest. Then push it back up. Consider using a spotter if you're lifting heavy weights.
activities.name: Incline Barbell Bench Press

activities.instructions: Lie down on a flat bench with one dumbbell in each hand. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them down towards your chest. Then push them back up. Tip: Kick the dumbbells up to starting position with the help of your thighs.
activities.name: Dumbbell Bench Press

activities.instructions: Lie down on a flat bench in a smith machine. Unhitch the barbell when you're ready and begin the movement by lowering it down towards your chest. Then push it back up.
activities.name: Smith Machine Bench Press

activities.instructions: Hang freely from a pull-up-bar and raise your legs straight forward as if you were doing a curl with your whole body.
activities.name: Hanging Leg Raise

activities.instructions: Stand on your knees in a cable machine with a cable attached to the handle. Grab the cable with both hands at the sides of your head. Pull the cable down as if you were doing an upside-down sit-up. Then let the cable back up. Keep hips stationary throughout the movement.
activities.name: Cable Crunch

activities.name: Barbell Wrist Curl

activities.instructions: Grab a weight plate in each hand so that you're holding it with your fingers only. Begin to walk and hold onto the plate for as long as you can.
activities.name: Farmer's Walk (with Weight Plate)

activities.instructions: Stand in a pulldown machine and grab the bar at a shoulder wide width. Begin pushing downwards with your arms straight throughout the movement, stop when you're about to reach your thighs.
activities.name: Straight-Arm Machine Lat Pulldown

Grab the wide pulldown bar with your palms facing forward at a little more than shoulder width apart. Slightly lean back so that you arch your lower back and puff your chest up, then pull the bar down by drawing your shoulders and upper arms down and back. Once the bar touches your chest, slowly begin to raise the bar back to the starting position, allowing your lat muscles to stretch out more the further up you go.
activities.name: Wide-Grip Machine Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Sit on the machine with the cable adjusted at its highest level. With a slight bend at your knees begin pulling towards your face until your upper arms form a T with the cable. Then lower it back down while keeping your upper body stationary.
activities.name: Machine Cable High Row

activities.instructions: Lie down flat on an incline bench with a barbell on the floor beneath the bench. Place a V handle at the end of the barbell and grab onto it. Pull it towards your abs and then lower it back down until it hits the floor again.
activities.name: Lying T-Bar Row

activities.instructions: Sit down on a bench in front of a cable machine. Pull the handle towards your lower belly while keeping your back straight. Then slowly let the handle back and let your arms stretch out fully.
activities.name: Cable Row

activities.instructions: Grab a barbell with a little wider than a shoulder width grip. While keeping your back straight and abs flexed, bend over until your back is at a 45 degree angle towards the floor. Pull the barbell towards your abs and stop when they touch, then let the barbell back down so you end up with your arms fully stretched out.
activities.name: Bent-Over Barbell Row

activities.instructions: Hang freely from a pull-up-bar with a little less than a shoulder width grip. Your palms should be facing forward, away from you. Pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar. Then lower yourself back down so that your arms are fully stretched.
activities.name: Close-Grip Pullup

activities.instructions: Stand up in a smith machine with a plate or some elevated object on the floor in front of you. Stand on it with the front of your foot and push yourself up through your foot. Then lower yourself back down. Tip: Stop for 1 second at the bottom of the movement.
activities.name: Smith Machine Calf Raise

activities.name: Machine Hack Squat

Press the sled all the way up and place one foot on the floor. Allow the sled weight to push the used leg down as far as comfortable and then push it back up until your leg is almost straight. That's a repetition. Switch leg after you've performed all repetitions for one leg.
activities.name: Single-Leg Press

performanceTarget.note: 1210 Just machine press feet touching, only toes on platform with heels hanging off

activities.instructions: Sit in the machine and adjust it so that you feel a minor stretch as you put your legs into the starting position. Push your legs together and then slowly let them back out again until you return to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Thigh Adduction (In)

activities.instructions: Sit comfortably in the machine and begin the movement by pushing your legs out to your sides as far as you can. Then return them to the starting position. All of this while keeping your upper body stationary.
activities.name: Machine Thigh Abduction (Out)

activities.instructions: Bend over and grab opposite cable handle in each hand. Begin to pull them to your sides in line with your shoulders until your arms are at shoulder level.
activities.name: Cable Rear Delt Fly

activities.name: Cable Back Fly

activities.name: Cable Side Raise

activities.name: Machine Leg Curl

activities.name: Bodyweight Bridge

activities.instructions: Sit comfortably in the machine and begin the movement by pushing your legs out to your sides as far as you can. Then return them to the starting position. All of this while keeping your upper body stationary.

activities.name: Bodyweight Squat

activities.name: Lying Barbell Skull Crusher

activities.instructions: Stand up right next to a cable machine with a bar attached to it. Grab it and keep your elbows tucked in to your sides, then simply curl the weight up to shoulder level. Lower it back down slowly until your arms are fully extended.
activities.name: Cable Curl

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a dumbbell. Position it at shoulder height then push it straight above your head so that your arm is straight. activities.name: Single-Arm Dumbbell Triceps Extension

activities.instructions: Grab a barbell with a reverse grip at shoulder width so that your palms are facing inwards against you. Let the barbell rest against your thighs at the bottom of the movement, then curl the weight up until it's at shoulder level. Lower it back down.

If you feel shoulder or elbow discomfort it is recommended to stop when your arms are at a 90 degree angle. Push yourself back up until your arms are straight. Machines can differ from each other but in general you should adjust the seat so that you're seated with your back against the padding and have the handles just below shoulder height. 

Grab onto them and push them in towards each other as if you were hugging someone in front of you. Pause when the handles reach each other and then slowly return them back to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Fly

performanceTarget.note: reverse pec deck rear delt fly 1212

activities.instructions: Lie down on a regular bench with one dumbbell in each hand. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them out to your sides. You can imagine yourself hugging a giant tree on the way up, and then letting go as you lower them down. Go all the way down until your elbows are at the same level as your body. Tip: Squeeze your chest together at the top of the movement as if you were squeezing a football!
activities.name: Dumbbell Fly

performanceTarget.note: bent over rear delt dumbbell fly 1012

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a cable handle. Raise it to your side until your arm is at shoulder level.
activities.name: Cable Side Raise

activities.instructions: Sit and grab the barbell with an underhand grip. Rest your arms on your thighs and let it roll all the way out to your fingers. Then squeeze it with your fingers so that the barbell ends up in the middle of your palm again.
activities.name: Barbell Wrist Curl

activities.instructions: Lie down on an inclined bench with one dumbbell in each hand. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them out to your sides. You can imagine yourself hugging a giant tree on the way up, and then letting go as you lower them down. Go all the way down until your elbows are at the same level as your body. Tip: Squeeze your chest together at the top of the movement as if you were squeezing a football!
activities.name: Incline Dumbbell Fly

activities.instructions: Lie down on an inclined bench under a barbell. Preferably in a rack for your own safety. Then un-rack the barbell and begin to lower it towards your upper chest. Then push it back up. Consider using a spotter if you're lifting heavy weights.
activities.name: Incline Barbell Bench Press

activities.instructions: Stand up in a smith machine with a plate or some elevated object on the floor in front of you. Stand on it with the front of your foot and push yourself up through your foot. Then lower yourself back down. Tip: Stop for 1 second at the bottom of the movement.
activities.name: Smith Machine Calf Raise

activities.instructions: Sit down with the pads on your upper thighs and unrack the weight. Lower it all the way down so that you feel a full stretch of your calves, then push it all the way up and return back down. Pause for a second or two in the bottom of the movement so that the weight doesn't get pushed up with the help of your achilles heel.
activities.name: Machine Calf Raise (Seated)

activities.instructions: Put something on the floor so that you can stand on it with the front of your foot as if you would be doing a regular calf raise. Grab onto something and bend over slightly, then begin the movement by pushing yourself up with one foot at a time. Lower yourself back down as far as you can and repeat.
activities.name: Donkey Calf Raise

activities.instructions: Stand up in the machine with the pads on your shoulders, unrack the weight and lower it all the way down so that you feel a good stretch in your calves. Push it all the way up and then lower it back down slowly, pausing at the bottom for a second or two to avoid pushing with your achilles heel.
activities.name: Machine Calf Raise

activities.instructions: Do a regular sit-up.
activities.name: Situp

activities.instructions: Stand on your knees in a cable machine with a cable attached to the handle. Grab the cable with both hands at the sides of your head. Pull the cable down as if you were doing an upside-down sit-up. Then let the cable back up. Keep hips stationary throughout the movement.
activities.name: Cable Crunch

activities.instructions: Lay down flat on the floor with your legs bent. Thrust your hips towards the ceiling as far as you can and keep it in the top position for a second or two. Then release it back down to the floor again. You've just completed a repetition.
activities.name: Bodyweight Bridge

performanceTarget.note: wrstling bridge, followed by 4x12 neck raises front and back

activities.instructions: Put the barbell on your upper back and squat down until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Barbell Squat

activities.instructions: Position the barbell on your upper chest and grab it with your palms facing upwards. Squat down until your legs are parallel to the floor and then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Barbell Front Squat

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine and put your feet up against the plate as if you were doing a Squat. Unrack the weight and lower it down until your knee is at a 90 degree angle, then push it back up. Stop just before your legs are fully straight to relieve your knees from extra stress.
activities.name: Machine Leg Press

performanceTarget.note: feet low and touching on platform

activities.instructions: Adjust the machine so that you're sitting comfortably and the seat ends just before your knee. Fully extend your legs while keeping the rest of your body stationary, then lower them back down to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Leg Extension

activities.instructions: Sit in the machine and adjust it so that you feel a minor stretch as you put your legs into the starting position. Push your legs together and then slowly let them back out again until you return to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Thigh Adduction (In)

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine and grab the handles at your sides. Place the padding just below your calves so that your legs are fully extended for the starting position. Curl them down until you have a 90 degree angle at your knee and then return back to the fully extended position.
activities.name: Machine Leg Curl

activities.instructions: Lie down on an inclined bench with one dumbbell in each hand. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them down towards your upper chest. Then push them back up. Tip: Kick the dumbbells up to starting position with the help of your thighs.
activities.name: Incline Dumbbell Bench Press

activities.instructions: Lie down on a flat bench with one dumbbell in each hand. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them down towards your chest. Then push them back up. Tip: Kick the dumbbells up to starting position with the help of your thighs.
activities.name: Dumbbell Bench Press

activities.instructions: Lie down on a declined bench with one dumbbell in each hand. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them down towards your lower chest. Then push them back up. Tip: Kick the dumbbells up to starting position with the help of your thighs.
activities.name: Decline Dumbbell Bench Press

activities.instructions: Lie down on a declined bench with one cable in each hand resting at your lower chest. Begin the movement by pushing them up to the starting position with your arms straight. Then begin to lower them out to your sides until your elbows are at the same level as your body, then push them back together. Tip: Squeeze your chest together at the top of the movement as if you were squeezing a football!
activities.name: Decline Cable Fly

activities.instructions: Stand in a dip station or between two steady bars. Grab the bars so that both your palms are facing inwards against you and begin the movement by lowering yourself down until your elbows are at shoulder level. Then push yourself back up.
activities.name: Chest Dip

activities.instructions: Lie down on a regular bench with one dumbbell in each hand. Get the dumbbells in position above your chest and then begin the movement by lowering them out to your sides. You can imagine yourself hugging a giant tree on the way up, and then letting go as you lower them down. Go all the way down until your elbows are at the same level as your body. Tip: Squeeze your chest together at the top of the movement as if you were squeezing a football!
activities.name: Dumbbell Fly

activities.instructions: Stand with one dumbbell in each hand so that they are touching your sides. While keeping your arms almost straight, raise the dumbbells up to the sides until they are just below shoulder level.
activities.name: Dumbbell Side Raise

activities.instructions: Sit on a bench and grab a dumbbell. Pull it out to your side until your arm is at shoulder level, and then lower it back down.
activities.name: Dumbbell Side Raise (Seated)

performanceTarget.note: dumbell shoulder raise 1 front 1 side 1 behind

activities.instructions: Grab a barbell with a little wider than a shoulder width grip. While keeping your back straight and abs flexed, bend over until your back is at a 45 degree angle towards the floor. Pull the barbell towards your abs and stop when they touch, then let the barbell back down so you end up with your arms fully stretched out.
activities.name: Bent-Over Barbell Row

activities.instructions: Stand up straight with a barbell resting on the floor just in front of you. Squat down and grab onto the bar just outside of your thighs, flex your abs and arch your back, then simply stand up. The bar should follow your thighs along the way.
activities.name: Barbell Deadlift

activities.instructions: Place yourself in a hyperextension machine and adjust it so that the pads end at your hips. Bend over until your lower back is fully stretched and then come back up. If you need more resistance you can hold onto a weight plate or a dumbbell.
activities.name: Machine Hyperextension

activities.instructions: Hang freely from a pull-up-bar with a little wider than shoulder width grip. Your palms should be facing forward, away from you. Pull yourself up until your chin is above the bar. Then lower yourself back down until your arms are fully stretched. See Weighted Pull-Ups if you are using additional weights.
activities.name: Pullup

activities.instructions: Adjust the machine so that your legs fit comfortably under the rack. Grab the bar and sit down with your legs under the rack. With a slight arch in your lower back begin pulling down towards your upper chest. After touching your chest with the bar, slowly return it until your arms and lats are fully stretched.
activities.name: Machine Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Adjust a pulldown machine and replace the bar with a V-Bar. Grab onto it and pull down towards your upper chest and then slowly let it back up until your arms are fully stretched.
activities.name: Machine V-Bar Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Stand in a pulldown machine and grab the bar at a shoulder wide width. Begin pushing downwards with your arms straight throughout the movement, stop when you're about to reach your thighs.
activities.name: Straight-Arm Machine Lat Pulldown

activities.instructions: Sit in the machine and adjust the pad so that you can reach the handles while your chest is pressed up against it. Grab the handles and begin pulling back. Try to keep your elbows as close to your sides as possible and imagine that you're pulling with your elbows, not your arms. Once you've reached as far back as you can go, slowly begin to let the handles back until your arms are fully stretched. Repeat.
activities.name: Machine Row

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a barbell at a little wider than shoulder width grip. Shrug the weight up and then lower it back down so that your arms are fully stretched. Try not to bend your arms as you do the movement.
activities.name: Barbell Shrug

activities.instructions: Stand up and grab a dumbbell in each hand. Shrug them up to your sides and then lower them back down until your arms are fully stretched. Try not to bend your arms as you do the movement.
activities.name: Dumbbell Shrug

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine with your shoulder blades squeezed together. Raise your shoulders as far up as you can and hold it for a couple of seconds. Then lower them back to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Shrug

activities.instructions: Stand up in a shoulder wide stance and grab the barbell at a shoulder wide grip. Bend over forward and lower the barbell all the way down as far as you can or until your back is parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Stiff-Leg Deadlift (Wide Stance)

activities.instructions: Place yourself under the barbell so that it is resting on your upper back. Keep everything stationary and begin to bend over, keeping your abs flexed. Stop when your torso is parallel to the floor and return to upright position.
activities.name: Good Mornings

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine and grab the handles at your sides. Place the padding just below your calves so that your legs are fully extended for the starting position. Curl them down until you have a 90 degree angle at your knee and then return back to the fully extended position.
activities.name: Machine Leg Curl

activities.instructions: Put the barbell on your upper back and squat down until your thighs are parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. Keep your back straight and abs flexed throughout the movement.
activities.name: Barbell Squat

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine and put your feet up against the plate as if you were doing a Squat. Unrack the weight and lower it down until your knee is at a 90 degree angle, then push it back up. Stop just before your legs are fully straight to relieve your knees from extra stress.
activities.name: Machine Leg Press

activities.instructions: Adjust the machine so that you're sitting comfortably and the seat ends just before your knee. Fully extend your legs while keeping the rest of your body stationary, then lower them back down to the starting position.
activities.name: Machine Leg Extension

activities.instructions: Sit comfortably in the machine and begin the movement by pushing your legs out to your sides as far as you can. Then return them to the starting position. All of this while keeping your upper body stationary.
activities.name: Machine Thigh Abduction (Out)

activities.instructions: Sit on a bench with back support. Grab one dumbbell in each hand and curl them up to your sides. Then lower them back down.
activities.name: Dumbbell Curl (Seated)

activities.instructions: Stand up with one dumbbell in each hand and get them to their starting positions right above your head by swinging them up. Your arms should be straight and pointing up. Slowly begin to lower them straight back with your elbows stationary throughout the movement. Lower them until they're at shoulder height. Then press them back up.
activities.name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension

activities.instructions: Rest your chest against the preacher pad. Grab an Ez-bar at the inner handle, your arms should be slightly rotated inwards from this grip. Lower the weight down until your arms are fully stretched and then curl the weight back up.
activities.name: EZ-Bar Preacher Curl

activities.instructions: Sit down on a regular bench with or without back support. Grab a pair of dumbbell and put them above your head so that your arms are straight. Begin the movement by lowering them back until they reach shoulder height, then push them back up until your arms are straight.
activities.name: Dumbbell Triceps Extension (Seated)

activities.instructions: Position yourself in front of a preacher bench so that you're looking at where you would usually sit. Grab the barbell from the seat and align your elbows with the padding of the bench and begin to curl. Use a shoulder wide grip.
activities.name: Spider Curl

activities.instructions: Lie down flat on a bench with a cable handle beneath your head. Grab onto the handle with both hands and push it upwards so that it ends up above your chest. Then lower it back down until your triceps are fully stretched out.
activities.name: Cable Lying Skull Crusher

activities.instructions: Grab a barbell with a reverse grip at shoulder width so that your palms are facing inwards against you. Let the barbell rest against your thighs at the bottom of the movement, then curl the weight up until it's at shoulder level. Lower it back down.
activities.name: Reverse Barbell Curl

activities.instructions: Stand in a cable machine with a bar attached to the handle. The handle should be at shoulder height. Grab it with overhand grip so that your palms are facing downwards towards the floor. Tuck your elbows in at your sides and push the bar down towards your thighs, then lower it back up.
activities.name: Cable Pushdown (with Bar Handle)

activities.instructions: Sit on a bench with one dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level. Press the dumbbells up over your head and then lower them back down until they're at shoulder level again.
activities.name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press (Seated)

activities.instructions: Stand with one dumbbell in each hand so that they are touching your sides. While keeping your arms almost straight, raise one dumbbell at a time to your side until it's just below shoulder level. Alternate arms between repetitions.
activities.name: Alternating Dumbbell Side Raise

activities.instructions: Stand up with a barbell resting on your upper chest. Keep your abs flexed and back straight as you press the weight straight up above your head, and then lower it back down.
activities.name: Barbell Shoulder Press

activities.instructions: Stand in a cable machine and grab the handle near one of your sides at a time. Pull it forward until it's at shoulder height and then lower it back down.
activities.name: Cable Front Raise

activities.name: Cable Crunch

activities.instructions: Lie down on the machine with the pads just below your calves and grab onto the handles at your sides. While keeping your upper legs static, curl the weight up as far as you can and keep your upper body stationary. Then lower the weight back down until your legs are fully stretched.
activities.name: Machine Lying Leg Curl

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine and grab the handles at your sides. Place the padding just below your calves so that your legs are fully extended for the starting position. Curl them down until you have a 90 degree angle at your knee and then return back to the fully extended position.
activities.name: Machine Leg Curl

Bend over forward and lower the barbell all the way down as far as you can or until your back is parallel to the floor. Then stand back up. activities.name: Stiff-Leg Deadlift (Wide Stance)

activities.instructions: Sit down in the machine with one resting on the floor and the other inside the machine. Curl the weight down as far as you can and squeeze your hamstrings as you do it, then let it back until your leg is fully extended. Switch leg after you've performed all repetitions with the other.
activities.name: Single-Leg Curl in Machine

Unrack the weight and lower it down until your knee is at a 90 degree angle, then push it back up. Stop just before your legs are fully straight to relieve your knees from extra stress.
activities.name: Machine Leg Press

activities.name: Smith Machine Squat
